<subSubSection pageId="98" pageNumber="669" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="98.[99,1302,3078,3466]" pageId="98" pageNumber="669">
Usually classified as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1850" box="[588,730,3113,3142]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Budorcas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="98" pageNumber="669" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="taxicolor">B. taxicolor</taxonomicName>
. The four takin species are differentiated on the basis of body color and mtDNA analysis of Chinese populations. Based on a phylogenetic study, takins are related to caprines and in particular to 
<taxonomicName box="[1078,1240,3188,3221]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Ammotragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="98" pageNumber="669" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ammotragus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[104,160,3227,3260]" class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Ovis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="98" pageNumber="669" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ovis</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
